nd derives from Old English <i>hēah</i> ‘high’ + <i>worthign</i> ‘enclosed settlement’."],"variants":[{"name":"Harden","meanings":["English: variant of   Arden   with prosthetic <i>H-</i>.","English: habitational name, either from Haredene Wood in East Tisbury (Wiltshire), or from Haredon (in Ugborough, Devon). The first placename probably derives from Old English <i>hara</i> ‘hare’ + <i>denu</i> ‘valley’. The second is from Old English <i>hara</i> + <i>dūn</i> ‘hare hill’.","English: variant of   Harding  ."]}]},{"name":"Ralph","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Ralf","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ralph de Arden was born about 1272, in Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Thomas de Arden, was 50 and his mother, Rose Vernon, was 34. He married Alice Beauchamp in 1297, in Drayton, Penkridge, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1320, in Drayton, Penkridge, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 49."},"et":{"Abt 1272–1320":"umbes 1272–1320","1272–1320":"1272–1320","1276–Female":"1276–Surnud","1290–1346":"1290–1346","1223–1306":"1223–1306","1240–1316":"1240–1316","about 1290":"umbes 1290","1297":"1297","1240":"1240","1272":"1272","Bef 1306":"enne 1306","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","Abt 1272":"umbes 1272","1346":"1346","about 1316":"umbes 1316","Bef 1267":"enne 1267","1223":"1223","1320":"1320","1276":